title: ICE on recursive type

labels.name: E-hard
labels.description: Call for participation: Experience needed to fix: Hard / a lot

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

body:
``` rust
enum FingerTree<A> {
    Empty,
    Single(A),
    Deep(Node<A>)
}

struct Node<A> {
    count: int,
    front: Digit<A>,
    inner: ~FingerTree<(A,A)>,
    back: Digit<A>
}

struct Digit<A> {
    count: int,
    content: [Option<A>, ..4]
}

fn FingerTree<A>() -> FingerTree<A> { Empty }
```

Note: `inner: ~FingerTree<(A,A)>,` seems to be the problematic bit.  If I make it `inner: ~FingerTree<A>,` it will compile.
